a

00:42:49.799 --> 00:42:58.730
very uniform roast. But you could argue that
that doesn't actually bring out the expression

00:42:58.730 --> 00:43:03.950
of every coffee. So every coffee could be
brought out with a slightly different roast.

00:43:03.950 --> 00:43:06.160
But that would be--

00:43:06.160 --> 00:43:11.150
&gt;&gt; Male #20: What was the tasting competition?
&gt;&gt;Alon: Huh?

00:43:11.150 --> 00:43:12.310
&gt;&gt; Male #20: The tasting competition?
&gt;&gt;Alon: The taste?

00:43:12.310 --> 00:43:13.699
&gt;&gt;Male #21: What does it take to be a tasting
champion?

00:43:13.699 --> 00:43:19.080
&gt;&gt; Alon: So what they do is, it's really
interesting. What they do is they give you

00:43:19.080 --> 00:43:22.599
triangulation tests. So they give you three
cups

00:43:22.599 --> 00:43:24.990
of coffee and two of them are identical and
one

00:43:24.990 --> 00:43:28.720
is different. So the trick is to guess which
one is different. So you have eight sets of

00:43:28.720 --> 00:43:32.230
three. And the person who guesses the most
is

00:43:32.230 --> 00:43:38.250
the winner. And if there's a tie, then time
matters. In fact, the Ritual Coffee here has

00:43:38.250 --> 00:43:43.359
like the 3-time U.S. champion Ben Kaminsky.
And

00:43:43.359 --> 00:43:47.500
actually, this year, it was really interesting
because there was this Greek guy who said,

00:43:47.500 --> 00:43:50.770
"you
know? I'm not going to taste. I'm just going

00:43:50.770 --> 00:43:57.600
to look." So he looked at the coffee and he
-- [mumbles inaudibly] --

00:43:57.600 --> 00:44:02.289
and this was very amusing in the first round.
And you can amusing in the second round. But

00:44:02.289 --> 00:44:08.990
he won the world championship [laughter] And
so, I was talking to the guy who invented

00:44:08.990 --> 00:44:10.580
the
competition right after that. He said, "well,

00:44:10.580 --> 00:44:15.920
we're changing the rules next year. And so,
what they're going to have is, they're going

00:44:15.920 --> 00:44:19.510
to -- first of all, the cups are not going
to

00:44:19.510 --> 00:44:23.350
be white. So they're going to be black. So
you can't actually see that much. And they're

00:44:23.350 --> 00:44:25.349
not going to have that much lighting on the
--.

00:44:25.349 --> 00:44:28.170
Male #22: Use blindfolds
[laughter]

00:44:28.170 --> 00:44:31.140
&gt;&gt;Alon: The thing is when he looked, he could
actually

00:44:31.140 --> 00:44:37.319
do it faster. So he actually won on time
against a guy who actually tasted the coffee.

00:44:37.319 --> 00:44:39.339
[laughter]
But it's interesting competition. It's really

00:44:39.339 --> 00:44:45.490
hard. Even the winners. The winner of the
world championship got four out of eight correct.

00:44:45.490 --> 00:44:54.119
